description.narrative: UNICEF interventions in education strengthened the national system's capacity to promote quality inclusive education (QIE). The framework for school desegregation (methodology for monitoring school segregation developed and approved by the National Commission on Preventing School Segregation and MoE) was strengthened. Public financing of education was significantly reinforced through passage of a law requiring financing of education for children aged 0-3 years and approval by the Ministry of National Education (MoE) of an action plan for revising the financing formula for pre-university education. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/01/2020
